                "subtype": "sidebar",
                "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                "image": {
                    "type": "image",
                    "name": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                },
                "html": "The banshee represents one of the most tragic of undead, a soul so wracked with agony and fury over a betrayal in life that, in death, it lingers on as a great evil. That most of those who become banshees were not evil in life only deepens this tragic theme, and many elven adventurers see it as their duty not only to put banshees to rest, but to right the wrong that saw their creation in the first place."
            }
        ],
